### Tested versions

- Reproducible in v4.6.dev5.official [f5918a9d3]

### System information

Godot v4.6.dev5 - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 1 monitor - Vulkan (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.7680) - 13th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-13600KF (20 threads) - 47.84 GiB memory

### Issue description

Some PropertyEditors have different heights which is not a problem, but once they are put in the same row, for example put in a HBoxContainer, it becomes a problem.

<img width="266" height="282" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f2852829-3901-44e9-86b6-bef2d543950d" />

### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a script, then copy this code to it. Then run (Ctrl+Shift+X) this script.
```
@tool
extends EditorScript

func _run() -> void:
	var dialog = AcceptDialog.new()
	dialog.hide()
	dialog.confirmed.connect(dialog.queue_free)
	dialog.canceled.connect(dialog.queue_free)
	dialog.close_requested.connect(dialog.queue_free)

	var vbox = VBoxContainer.new()
	dialog.add_child(vbox)

	var hbox = HBoxContainer.new()
	vbox.add_child(hbox)

	var foo = Foo.new()
	var props = foo.get_property_list().filter(func(v): return v.name == "option" or v.name == "a")
	for p in props:
		var editor = EditorInspector.instantiate_property_editor(foo, p.type, p.name, p.hint, p.hint_string, p.usage)
		editor.label = p.name
		editor.size_flags_horizontal = Control.SIZE_EXPAND_FILL
		hbox.add_child(editor)

	EditorInterface.popup_dialog_centered(dialog, Vector2i(500, 500))

class Foo:
	@export_enum("A", "B") var option: String
	@export var a: String

```

